# PRIME v2 Agent Workflow

Before implementing any change, follow [docs/agents/DEVELOPMENT-FLOW.md](docs/agents/DEVELOPMENT-FLOW.md).

**Intern / vibe coding:** state current phase and follow [INTERN-VIBE-CODING-GUIDE.md](docs/agents/INTERN-VIBE-CODING-GUIDE.md). No app code before Phase 4 approval.

## Required consultations (do not skip)

1. **Product Manager** — confirm scope, user story, acceptance criteria
2. **Architect** — confirm design, modules, ADRs if needed
3. **Security** — confirm RBAC, validation, secrets, audit impact
4. **QA** — define tests before coding; run tests before push

Route to domain lead: **Frontend** (UI), **Backend** (API/workflow), **Database** (schema), **DevOps** (deploy/CI).

## When the user asks to code

1. State which agents must approve the task.
2. Ask clarifying questions if user story, permissions, or workflow status are missing.
3. Do not implement until scope/design/security/tests are clear (Phase 0: no coding until MVP/architecture approved).

## PRIME constraints (always)

- Never bypass role checks or overwrite submitted proposal versions.
- Never expose private RTEC comments to applicants.
- Never commit secrets.

See [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) and [README.md](README.md) §32–33.
